fields.ingredients:
2 steaks, a pound each. If you don’t rush, wrap the meat into a cotton cloth, place on a grid so that the air would have access to meat from all sides, and put everything into a fridge for 3-4 days. Change the cloth daily and let the meat be of a room temperature by the time of cooking;
1 tbsp of olive oil;
50 g of butter;
1 tbsp of salt;
1 tsp of northern spices;
1 clove of garlic. Crushed;
1-2 cloves of garlic. Whole;
1 glass of red dry wine ~ 230 ml;

fields.cooking_step:
Prepare the meat for the cooking, but do not wash it, as the surface must be dry;

Mix salt, northern spices and chopped garlic. Rub the meat with this mixture from all sides;

Preheat the frying pan with olive oil and butter. I use a large cast-iron frying pan with a grill for that purposes;

Gently place the steaks in a pan and cook for 2.5 minutes. Turn over and cook for another 2.5 minutes;

At this point, I add a couple of crushed garlic cloves and, using a long teaspoon, pour the oil over the steaks. You can pour it all the way while the meat is being cooked. This is quite a pleasant and meditative activity.

My steaks were thick enough, so I took the tongs and cooked for another minute from all sides. All this time we cook on high fire;

Now gently pour the wine — it should start hissing and expressing its displeasure. Cook for 2-3 minutes to get medium-rare. Then you can either remove the meat, put it a warm plate, cover it with foil and let it rest for 10 minutes, or cook 3-5 minutes more till your favorite degree of readiness, turning one or two times;

Reduce the heat to medium and boil the liquid to the state of the sauce. Cook for 6-10 minutes, stirring occasionally. I usually add a small piece of butter to this sauce;
This steak goes well with grilled vegetable or sauteed carrots, about which I have already written.

Technical issues and replacements:

No recommendations for meat, as everyone benefits from their preferences. Any piece of beef, from which you can prepare a steak, would do.
I have a large cast-iron frying pan. It can hold up to two pieces of meat freely. It is important to cook on a high fire. If the temperature drops, the meat will no longer be roasted, but stewed;
I have already written about smoked salt in the recipe of Forest Strider Drumstick. Please, read it or just replace the smoked salt with sea salt.

fields.ingredients:
Ingredients for the dough:

400 g flour;
200 g of butter;
A couple of pinches of salt;
10-12 tbsp. ice water.
Ingredients for the filling:

400-450 g pitted cherries. If you take out a pit, be careful — we need a whole beautiful cherry. Both frozen and fresh cherries will do the thing. In the case of frozen cherries, remove it from the freezer in advance so that it has time to completely thaw and become a room temperature. Save the juice!
100-150 ml of cherry juice;
170-200 g of sugar;
3 tbsp cornstarch;
2 tsp of cinnamon;
1/2 tsp ground cardamom;
1/2 tsp ground ginger;
1 scrambled egg with 1 tsp water for greasing.

fields.cooking_step:
Put water in the freezer;
Place the flour in a large bowl or sprinkle over a large cutting board;
Salt the flour and add the cold diced butter. I also put a knife in the fridge in advance to quickly cut the butter. Mix the butter with the flour and chop with knives or fork. You’ll need a medium-sized crumb
When the mixture is done, make a hole in it and pour the icy water. Knead like a regular dough. No need to stretch. In the end, you’ll need a ball-shaped dough. Ingredients must be cold. For more confidence from time to time I place my hands under cold running water;
Divide the dough somewhere 60/40 (bottom and lid). Roll out a larger piece so that it becomes a little bigger than your baking pan. Spread the dough over the pan, adjusting it with your fingers. Cover with a plastic film and put into the fridge for half an hour;
Take the pan out and pierce the dough with a fork. We do this to prevent hot steam from inflating the dough. The second piece of dough is still in the fridge;
Cover the bottom with baking paper and pour a thick layer of beans. Put the pan into a 200 C oven for 15 minutes;
Remove the load and bake for another 10 minutes to dry the bottom;
Remove the pan and let rest and cool for 10 minutes;
Drain the cherries from the juice. In a suitable saucepan, mix the cherries with sugar, starch, and spices. Pour the juice. Gently stir;
Put on a medium heat and cook for 5 minutes, stirring to dissolve the sugar;
Let the cherries rest for 5 minutes and gently pour on the cake, distributing the berries;
While the cherries cool, roll out the dough and cut it into strips. Spread the strips over the cake, pressing a little. I made the edges to remove the bumps. Grease the strips with egg and water, avoiding the filling;
Bake for 20-25 minutes;
Now the most difficult thing. Let the cake cool down for at least an hour or two so that the filling got the desired texture. After that, you can cut and eat.

Replacements:

You can take a ready-made dough from a supermarket. I tried to bake the cake this way and it turned out great;
Cherries can be replaced by blueberries, currants and other favorite berries with a sour tint;
Part of the cherry juice or the whole juice can be changed to red dry wine or accompanied with brandy. It will be even more intense;
Cornstarch can be replaced with potato starch.
